  "body": "Previously, `BufWriter::write` would just return an `std::io::OtherIoError` if someone attempted to write past the end of the wrapped buffer. This pull request changes the error to support partial writes and return a `std::io::ShortWrite`, or an `io::io::EndOfFile` if it's been fully exhausted.\n\n I've also optimized away a bounds check inside `BufWriter::write`, which should help shave off some nanoseconds in an inner loops.\n",
